atrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Dilip, Anirban, Gopal, Alok, Anindya, Arunava, Asit, Asok, Dibyendu, Goutam, Indra, Indranil.","Indian: variant of   Dey  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Dey","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Ashit, Indu, Naina, Partha, Soumya, Ajit, Anjan, Anjana, Anup, Arjun, Arun, Ashim.","English, Scottish, and Welsh: variant of   Day  .","German: topographic name from a field name in North Rhine-Westphalia, denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"Sherburne","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English (Lancashire): habitational name from any of several places called with Old English <i>scīr</i> ‘bright, clear’ + <i>burna</i> ‘stream’, including Sherburn in Elmet (Yorkshire), Sherburn (East Yorkshire, Durham), Shirburn (Oxfordshire), Sherborne (Dorset, Gloucestershire), Sherborne Saint John, Monk Sherborne (Hampshire), Sherbourne (Warwickshire), Sherbourne in Albury (Surrey), and Sherborne in Litton (Somerset). This surname is now rare in Britain."],"variants":[{"name":"Sherburn","meanings":["English: variant of   Sherburne  ."]},{"name":"Sherbon","meanings":["English: variant of   Sherburne   with loss of the second <i>-r-</i> by dissimilation. This form of the surname is now rare in Britain."]}]},{"name":"Thomas","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["New Testament name, borne by one of Christ's twelve apostles, referred to as ‘Thomas, called Didymus’ (John 11:16; 20:24). <i>Didymos</i> is the Greek word for ‘twin’, and the name is the Greek form of an Aramaic byname meaning ‘twin’. The given name has always been popular throughout Christendom, in part because St Thomas's doubts have made him seem a very human character."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Thomas de Sherburne was born in 1246, in Sherburn Village, Durham, England, United Kingdom, his father, Robert de Sherburne, was 42 and his mother, Marilda FitzAdam de Catford, was 24. He married Lady Thomas Sherburn in 1270, in Manchester, Lancashire, England. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter. He died in 1272, in Clitheroe, Lancashire, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 26."},"et":{"1246–1272":"1246–1272","1245–1292":"1245–1292","1258–Male":"1258–Surnud","1250–Female":"1250–Surnud","1272–Female":"1272–Surnud","1205–1261":"1205–1261","1223–1261":"1223–1261","1205":"1205","Abt 1272":"umbes 1272","1258":"1258","1246":"1246","1223":"1223","1245":"1245","1261":"1261","1272":"1272","1250":"1250","1270":"1270","1292":"1292","Of Barlow, Chorlton, Lancashire, England":"Chorlton cum Hardy, Lancashire, England","Clitheroe, Lancashire, England":"Clitheroe, Lancashire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Sherburn Village, Durham, England":"Sherburn Village, Durham, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Sherburn, Durham, England":"Sherburn Village, Durham, England","Manchester, Lancashire, England":"Manchester, Lancashire, England","Lancashire, England":"Lancashire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1246–1272":"1246–1272","1245–1292":"1245–1292","1258–Male":"1258–Kuollut","1250–Female":"1250–Kuollut","1272–Female":"1272–Kuollut","1205–1261":"1205–1261","1223–1261":"1223–1261","1205":"1205","Abt 1272":"noin 1272","1258":"1258","1246":"1246","1223":"1223","1245":"1245","1261":"1261","1272":"1272","1250":"1250","1270":"1270","1292":"1292","Of Barlow, Chorlton, Lancashire, England":"Chorlton cum Hardy, Lancashire, England","Clitheroe, Lancashire, England":"Clitheroe, Lancashire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Sherburn Village, Durham, England":"Sherburn Village, Durham, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Sherburn, Durham, England":"Sherburn Village, Durham, England","Manchester, Lancashire, England":"Manchester, Lancashire, England","Lancashire, England":"Lancashir